<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="fall-n">fall <strong><em>n</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /fɔːl/    美 /fɔːl/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-c">1.★ <strong>[C] 落下；跌倒；(雨 、雪等) 的降落：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A fall into the pit, a gain in your wit.
吃一堑，长一智。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The fall from his horse hurt him.
他从马背上跌下来受了伤。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a heavy fall of rain / snow
一场大雨/雪</p></div>

<h4 id="2-c">2.★ <strong>[C] (温度、价格等) 下降；(风势、声音等) 减弱：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>There was a sudden fall in temperature.
气温突然下降。</p></div>

<h4 id="3-u">3.★ <strong>[U] 沦陷；衰亡：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>the rise and fall of UK
大英帝国的兴衰</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>I am awfully tired, but I know I'll never fall sleep.  （2013 浙江 改错）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. sleep → asleep  </p></div>